author: Susannah Luthi
title: Early efforts to halt virus spread may have spared some states, CDC says
description: Areas that closed schools early and enforced strict social distancing may have avoided the brunt of new cases.
content:
In the seven days before April 7, when the virus accelerated in the U.S., Minnesota had 8.3 infections per 100,000 while New York City had 418.
